title: Murder in the Sacristy
creator: Daniel A. Lord
description: LibriVox recording of MURDER IN THE SACRISTY, by DANIEL A. LORD, S.J.. Read by Maria Therese A sacristan is found murdered in the sacristy and the safe robbed of valuable jewels. All clues seem to point to the priest as the murderer. But is the priest the guilty party - or is it the communist? - the nazi? - the Senator's wife? --- or someone else? This mystery novel, set in World War II Chicago, was written by Daniel A Lord, S.J., who was a priest and popular American Catholic writer. The subjects of the works in his bibliography range from religion, humor, plays, songs, mysteries and even politics. His most influential work was possibly in drafting the 1930 Production Code for motion pictures. (Introduction by Maria Therese) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (91MB)
subject: librivox; audiobook; mystery; murder; Catholic; priest; communism; nazi; world war II
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody:
The summary covers the plot, and listen carefully to those last few chapters, because you are going to get a really unexpected twist.  :-)  

Reader = excellent!  Story = excellent!  Enjoy!
